al resistance hampered the integration of women's rights into the organization's overall work.  afunded by Swiss National Science Foundation (SNSF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aFeminism. 0aWomen's rights. 4aCivil Society. 4aGender Studies. 4aHuman Rights Organizations. 4aHuman Rights. 4aLaw. 4aNetworks. 4aPolitical Science. 4aPolitics. 4aSocial Movements. 4aWomen's Rights. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Human Rights.2bisacsh  aCivil Society.  aHuman Rights Organizations.  aHuman Rights.  aLaw.  aNetworks.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitics.  aSocial Movements.  aWomen's Rights.2 aSwiss National Science Foundation (SNSF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2021z97831107673150 cprintz978383766008140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839460085?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839460085zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839460085/original  a978-3-11-074335-7 DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  a978-3-11-076731-5 transcript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA